width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uhoraciofv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HoracioFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/21/02 6:31:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> well</span><hr size=1> I use it to shut off all and any damage delt by me and other player's. The only thing's I see are npc's begining to cast spell's (so I can Slam at the apropriate time) and all group chat or raid chat. I really have no need to see damage im taking or damage im dealing. My health is the concern of the healer's the mob's health I can see by the little red bar. And if I see the &quot;so and so's spell is interupted I know if my bash landed. If im out soloing I turn my damage back on just fer kick's though. But I can say it helps to reduce lag considerably... or seem's to at least. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umixxibixiebane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mixxi Bixiebane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/21/02 2:52:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: well</span><hr size=1> Hmm. I use the hits to let me know who is getting hit (and who I need to pull mobs off of) and to make sure that my party is hitting the things they should be hitting (or if they need a gentle assist reminder). But I'm worried that spreading all the information out will just make it more easy to miss something.<br><br>And in asking this question, I'm surprised at how many warriors use the health bars as a way to see if someone is getting aggro. I always use the combat text to keep tabs on this, since then I know WHAT is hitting them and if it's a huge emergency or just an annoyance.<br><br>--Mixxi Moondreamer<br>Halfling warrior in the service of Brell <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukratetheswifttail.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krate The Swift Tail</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/thrawk/Krate.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/21/02 4:55:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: well</span><hr size=1> Hate Hate Hate it.  I think there is a bug that prevents some people from seeing the procs and spell cast graphics and messages of Pet's, PC's and NPC's.  This is very bad for a Monk that is trying to split casters with FD.  There is a big thread about this on Monkly-Business. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uhoraciofv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HoracioFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/22/02 5:41:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hmm</span><hr size=1> I usually watch everyones red bar's to see if sombody is taking damage who shouldn't be. And usually its pretty easy to tell wich mob it is... the one that isnt in front of you anymore and is standing 10 ft away beating on your cleric would prolly be the one. Using combat text is not verry reliable.. I mean come on just with other's damage turned on (not people taking damage mind you) Its scrolls so fast it's just a big blur nothing is discernable until the mob is dead. Another thing is position yourself on the other side of the mob's so you can see your party. This is the easyest way to tell cause you can phisicly watch them run over and start beating on sombody else. Imho text dose nothing but make thing's harder expecialy for a warrior. Cut's way down on comunication and comunication is probably the #1 most important thing in any group hands down. Sure its nice to be able to see what everyone is hitting for but its more detrimental to the party then it is helpfull. But im sure everyone has thier own opinion's on what is best. So whatever work's for you prolly is the best method for you to use since your comfortable with it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/23/02 1:48:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hmm</span><hr size=1> Well, it's a godsend to me... I turned off others hits and spells and such a LONG time ago, since I was spamming myself silly.  Now I can put my own damage elsewhere, and actually read what people say to me... being a rogue with silver chitten handwraps, a 22 delay primary weapon, and a 20 delay offhand makes for some SERIOUS battle spam.  I can finally read!  Who knows, maybe I'll put others' hits in a new window too.  <br><br>Jarkell Ravensteel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxenojones.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XENOJONES</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/23/02 4:32:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hmm</span><hr size=1> I keep my hits on, but have others turned off. It is a problem at times since with my level, dual wield, almost always hasted and having an 18 delay weapon I seriously spam myself, but when my screen starts going all red then I know something is wrong like ENRAGE! Nothing is fine as to be at full hitpoints missing an enrage and popping like a Junebug hitting the windshield of a speed Peterbuilt on an Illinois highway. Also I keep my spell effects on so I can see when a mob starts to cast, what spells are landing on it etc.....<br>I may miss alot of tells, but I have more success.<br><br><br>Rollen Zekson<br>Warlord of Resolution <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/24/02 3:49:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hmm</span><hr size=1> Enrage + Brittle Haste Poison + High Level Damage Shield = Fun!<br><br>Jarkell Ravensteel <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><t